<h2>Google Business Profile: Your Most Important Asset</h2>
<p>Your <a href="/blog/optimize-google-business-profile/">Google Business Profile</a> (GBP) is the single most important ranking factor for local daycare searches. GBP signals account for 32% of <a href="/glossary/local-ranking-factors/">local ranking factors</a>. That makes your profile more influential than your website, backlinks, and citations combined.</p>
<h3>Claim and Verify Your Profile</h3>
<p>If you have not claimed your GBP, do it today at business.google.com. Choose "Child Care Agency" as your primary category. Add secondary categories like "Preschool," "Day Care Center," and "After School Program" if applicable.</p>
<h3>Optimize Every Field</h3>
<p>Complete profiles appear in 70% more discovery searches than incomplete ones. Fill in every field:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Business name:</strong> Your exact legal name. Do not keyword-stuff. "Sunshine Daycare" is correct. "Sunshine Daycare Best Childcare Center Dallas TX" gets flagged.</li>
<li><strong>Address:</strong> Your physical location where parents drop off children.</li>
<li><strong>Service areas:</strong> List your city and neighboring zip codes.</li>
<li><strong>Phone number:</strong> A local number builds trust. Parents want to call a local center, not a toll-free line.</li>
<li><strong>Business hours:</strong> Accurate drop-off and pickup hours. Update for holidays.</li>
<li><strong>Business description:</strong> 750 characters. Include your city, age groups served, and programs naturally.</li>
<li><strong>Services:</strong> Add every program individually. Infant care, toddler program, preschool, after-school, summer camp.</li>
<li><strong>Photos:</strong> Upload 20+ high-quality photos. Classrooms, playground, staff, meals, and activities.</li>
</ul>
<p>GBP listings with over 100 photos get 1,065% more clicks than the average listing. Parents want to see where their children will spend the day. Show clean classrooms, engaged teachers, and happy kids (with parent permission for child photos).</p>
<h3>Post Regularly</h3>
<p>GBP posts signal activity to Google and engage parents. Post 2 to 3 times per week. Share curriculum highlights, seasonal activities, enrollment openings, and parent tips. For a complete posting strategy, see our <a href="/blog/gbp-posting-frequency/">GBP posting frequency guide</a>.</p>
<h3>Respond to Every Review</h3>
<p>Response rate matters for rankings and for parents. Respond to every review within 24 hours. Thank positive reviewers by name. Address negative reviews professionally and empathetically. Use our <a href="/tools/review-response-generator/">review response generator</a> to save time while maintaining a personal tone.</p>
