<h2>Technical SEO for Daycare Websites</h2>
<p>Technical issues kill daycare websites silently. A slow site, broken mobile layout, or missing schema prevents everything else from working.</p>
<h3>Site Speed</h3>
<p>Parents searching on their phones expect fast results. Compress every image. Use WebP format. Target under 3 seconds for full page load on mobile. Google Core Web Vitals measure loading performance, and slow sites rank lower.</p>
<h3>Mobile Optimization</h3>
<p>Over 70% of daycare searches happen on mobile devices. Parents searching during lunch breaks or after bedtime are almost always on their phones. Your entire site must work on a 375px-wide screen. Test every page on your phone. Tap targets must be large enough for one-hand use.</p>
<h3>Schema Markup</h3>
<p>Add <a href="/blog/schema-markup-seo-guide/">schema markup</a> to tell Google exactly what your center offers:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>ChildCare</strong> schema (the specific schema.org type for daycare centers) with your name, address, phone, hours, age ranges, and pricing</li>
<li><strong>LocalBusiness</strong> schema with service area and operating hours</li>
<li><strong>Review</strong> schema to display star ratings in search results</li>
<li><strong>FAQ</strong> schema on pages with frequently asked questions</li>
<li><strong>Event</strong> schema for open houses, parent workshops, and community events</li>
</ul>
<p>The ChildCare schema type is specific to daycare and childcare facilities. It supports properties like "age range," "opening hours," and "number of employees." Most daycare websites do not use it. Adding it gives you an edge in search results.</p>
<h3>SSL and Security</h3>
<p>Every page must load over HTTPS. Parents researching daycare centers will not fill out a tour request form on an unsecured site. The "Not Secure" warning in Chrome destroys trust instantly for a parent about to share their contact information and child details.</p>
<h3>Run an SEO Audit</h3>
<p>Before investing in content or links, identify what is broken on your site. Use our free <a href="/tools/seo-audit/">SEO audit tool</a> to scan for technical issues, or follow our complete <a href="/blog/how-to-do-seo-audit/">SEO audit guide</a>.</p>
