<h2>FAQ</h2>
<p><strong>How much does SEO cost for a daycare center?</strong></p>
<p>DIY SEO costs $0 to $300 per month for tools. Hiring a freelancer runs $500 to $2,000 per month. Full-service local SEO agencies charge $1,500 to $5,000 per month. Stacc offers blog SEO starting at $99 per month and local SEO starting at $49 per month, covering content publishing and <a href="/glossary/gbp-optimization/">GBP management</a>.</p>
<p><strong>How long does it take for daycare SEO to work?</strong></p>
<p>Expect initial ranking movement within 60 to 90 days. Consistent tour requests typically start at 4 to 6 months. Full local market dominance takes 12+ months of sustained effort. Smaller markets see faster results. See our guide on <a href="/blog/how-long-seo-takes/">how long SEO takes</a> for detailed timelines.</p>
<p><strong>What is the best Google Business Profile category for a daycare?</strong></p>
<p>Use "Child Care Agency" as your primary category. Add "Day Care Center," "Preschool," and "After School Program" as secondary categories. The primary category carries the most ranking weight for local searches.</p>
<p><strong>Should a daycare center have a blog?</strong></p>
<p>Yes. Blog content drives organic traffic, builds authority, and creates internal links to your program pages. Centers that publish 4+ posts per month rank for 3x more keywords than centers with static websites. Each post creates another opportunity to appear in search results and AI Overviews.</p>
<p><strong>What are the most important keywords for daycare SEO?</strong></p>
<p>Start with high-intent local keywords: "daycare in [city]," "preschool near me," and "childcare [city]." Then target program keywords: "infant care [city]," "after-school program near me." Finally, build authority with informational content: "when to start daycare," "daycare vs preschool," and "how to choose a daycare."</p>
<p><strong>How do reviews affect daycare SEO rankings?</strong></p>
<p><a href="/glossary/google-reviews/">Google reviews</a> are a top-3 <a href="/glossary/local-ranking-factors/">local ranking factor</a>. Review quantity, quality, velocity, and response rate all influence your position in the local pack. For daycare centers specifically, reviews also serve as the primary trust signal for parents making enrollment decisions. A center with 80+ reviews at 4.5 stars will outrank and outconvert a center with 5 reviews at 5.0 stars.</p>
